***********[TROUBLESHOOTING]************
****************************************

MOST ISSUES CAN BE RESOLVED BY REPAIRING YOUR 'appConfig.ini' FILE. 

	------------A LIST OF ITEMS---------------
	-------TO CHECK IN THE CONFIG FILE:-------

	1.) VERIFY THAT PATHS ARE ACCESSIBLE TO THE PROGRAM AND IN FILE EXPLORER.
		a. ENSURE PROPER PERMISSIONS**.
		b. CONFIRM NAVIGABLE PATHS IN FILE EXPLORER.
	2.) 'CURRENT WORLD NAME' SHOULD HAVE THE CORRECT MAP NAME ('world') IN THE MAIN SERVER
	    FILES DIRECTORY.
	3.) CONFIRM THAT 'EXECUTABLE' HAS A VALID PATH TO A MINECRAFT SERVER .JAR OR .BAT FILE.
		a. IF BLANK, THE 'MINECRAFT SERVER FILES' PATH MAY BE INCORRECT OR MISSING A LAUNCH 
		   EXECUTABLE.
		b. IF INCORRECT (FROM BUILT-IN SEARCH), THERE MAY BE MULTIPLE '.bat' OR '.jar' FILES IN THE 
		   MAIN MINECRAFT SERVER DIRECTORY.
	4.) FOR SUBSEQUENT LAUNCHES, ENSURE 'FTL' IS SET TO 'FALSE'.


**IF ALL ELSE FAILS, RUN AS ADMINISTRATOR

	----------RESETTING THE PROGRAM---------

TO RESET THE PROGRAM, DELETE THE 'appConfig.ini' FILE FROM THE LAUNCH EXECUTABLE PATH.





